modules.description: This module generates and manipulates 128-bit identifiers through hashing algorithms, randomization, timestamp-based logic, and custom templates. It handles UUIDs alongside auxiliary types like timestamps, bitfields, and string/binary encodings, supporting operations to create, parse, compare, and convert them. Key applications include producing deterministic identifiers from names (MD5/SHA-1), generating secure random IDs, creating time-ordered UUIDs with monotonic counters, and interoperating across different endianness or serialization formats.
